goals.goalText: Austria actively engages on regional and global challenges as a reliable partner in law enforcement and national security endeavors.
The Austrian public supports and trusts United States policies and values.
Austria contributes to economic growth in the United States and worldwide.

Mission provides outstanding service to official and private American citizens present in Austria, Austrian citizens, and third-country nationals residing in Austria, as well as support services to other Embassies in the region.
Spur Sustained Equitable Economic Growth and Development
Advance Peace & Security
Stronger Democratic Institutions, Improved Governance & Respect of Human Rights
The United States and Brazil Develop Global Partnerships
The United States and Brazil Build an Economic Relationship for the 21st Century
The United States and Brazil Expand People-to-People Relationships
The United States and Brazil Build Lasting Partnerships to Ensure our Citizens' Security
The Governments of the United States and Brazil Deepen Institutional Engagement
Botswana's democratic institutions are strong and accountable, and the government respects the human rights of all its citizens.
Botswana diversifies its economy and enjoys sustained, private sector-led economic growth fueled, in part, by trade and investment from American companies.

Botswana partners with the United States to prevent, mitigate, and resolve armed conflict; counter transnational threats; and, advance regional security cooperation, including law enforcement cooperation.
Botswana's health system is capable of meeting the country's long-term health challenges, and Botswana's youth enjoy opportunities to participate in the country's political and economic future.
Chile assumes increased regional and global leadership, reinforced by growing bilateral cooperation that benefits both countries.
U.S. citizens are protected, and U.S. borders remain secure, while legitimate travel is facilitated.

Strengthening Democratic Institutions

As Europe's largest economy and a key transatlantic partner, Germany actively engages in the full-spectrum of global diplomatic and security challenges -- leveraging its unique diplomatic, development, and economic clout to pursue our shared objectives.
Germany works closely with the United States globally for economic prosperity and stability.
Germany is a more effective and predictable partner on counterterrorism and is a force multiplier for U.S. security and non-proliferation goals.
The German public understands and supports USG foreign policy objectives and Mission goals, and contributes to a vital transatlantic partnership.
Mission provides professional, first-class service to official and private Americans present in Germany, employing tools available to a 21st century workforce.
Strengthen the partnership between the USG and the GOS and GOA around a shared global agenda.
Build public support for U.S. foreign policy and project American values.
Practice economic statecraft to promote sustainable Spanish economic growth and increase trade and investment.
Protect the safety and security of American Citizens in Spain, Andorra, and at home.

Burma adopts legitimate and sustainable processes which enable domestic stakeholders to pursue national reconciliation consistent with U.S. Government interests in supporting the establishment of a stable, inclusive union necessary to the durability of democratic reforms

Burma is moving towards a well-governed democratic state that is inclusive, accountable, and responsive to its people, in line with U.S. interests in promoting freedom and democracy and protecting human rights

Burma has the legal and regulatory environment, institutions, and human capital required to increase trade, investment, and competitiveness for the benefit of the people of Burma, the region, and the United States
Burmese people, households, communities, and systems are more stable, cohesive, and healthy

Burma becomes an active international partner that upholds commitments and makes use of multilateral fora such as the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) to increase cooperation to address nonproliferation, security, and transnational challenges and opportunities in furtherance of U.S. values and objectives

Malaysia facilitates U.S. engagement with ASEAN and contributes to a more cohesive and effective ASEAN that strengthens regional stability, integration, and connectivity

The United States and Thailand sustain and expand their bilateral cooperation within Thailand and the sub-region while Thailand takes a greater leadership role in addressing regional and global challenges and strengthening regional institutions to achieve mutual interests

The U.S.-Thailand economic partnership leverages Thailand's position as a strategic hub in Asia to benefit the U.S. economy and U.S. businesses by promoting transparent, accountable, consistent business practices perpetuating high environmental standards and good labor practices throughout the region

Thailand achieves an increasingly strong, functional democracy with government institutions that are responsive to its people's needs, aspirations, and economic well-being through U.S.-Thai partnership in support of the rule of law and human security

The Thai public values the strong, multifaceted U.S.-Thai partnership at all levels, and it shares with the United States a commitment to democratic governance and observance of human rights, thereby advancing U.S. interests in Thailand and the region
Mission Thailand provides professional, first-rate services to meet the growing needs of U.S. citizens traveling, conducting business, or living in Thailand

Armenia engages with its neighbors to achieve peace and greater regional integration, strengthens its security partnership with the U.S. and NATO, and protects U.S. citizens in Armenia.
Armenia creates a resilient and energy secure economic environment which fosters sustained economic growth and provides increased opportunities for U.S. business and investment.
The Government of Armenia implements a Western-oriented reform program that leads to a more just, pluralistic society with democratic accountability, free and fair elections, and rule of law.
Promote open government and countering corruption as key components in achieving our strategic vision of a Europe whole, free, and at peace.

The U.S.-Australia alliance remains a vital and enduring partnership that strategically and materially deters and defends against threats to Australia, the region, and to the United States. Our two countries work together to build Australian and regional capacity, resolve regional and global disputes peacefully, and confront emerging challenges. Australia continues to be an important contributor to regional peace and security, working closely with the U.S. in developing solutions to emerging threats to our national security.

U.S. prosperity and inclusive economic growth advances by expanding both the scope of U.S. goods and services exports to Australia, and two-way investment flows, in order to develop closer regional economic integration that increases the quantity and quality of trade and strengthens our partnerships with emerging economies

Based on a sound understanding of U.S. policies, society, and values, a solid majority of the Australian public – especially youth audiences – supports U.S. global leadership and the bilateral partnership as key to security and economic prosperity worldwide and in the Asia-Pacific

Mission Australia advances cooperation on the global challenges of the 21st century by working with the Australian government to develop the strategies and architecture that will enhance regional cooperation on a wide range of issues, including the environment, science and technology, agriculture, human rights, and economic development, food security, and disaster preparedness
Mission Australia provides professional, first-class service to official and private Americans present in Australia, employing tools available to a 21st-century workforce

Azerbaijan's highly developed and well-secured energy resources contribute to the development of a diversified economy, and European energy security.
